sense_1:
rise in rank or status
(Example: Her new novel jumped high on the bestseller list)
sense_2:
start (a car engine whose battery is dead) by connecting it to another car's battery
(Example: Can you give me a jump, my battery is dead)
sense_3:
jump from an airplane and descend with a parachute
(Example: Your first time jumping will be tandem)
sense_4:
pass abruptly from one state or topic to another
(Example: Jump to a conclusion)
sense_5:
run off or leave the rails
(Example: The train jumped the tracks)
